I'm Ellen Mitchell, and here's your nightly guide to the latest developments at the Pentagon, on Capitol Hill and beyond.
Brett Crozier was sent to three admirals and copied to seven other captains, according to a copy obtained by The Washington Post.
Attached to the email was the letter Crozier wrote pleading for help because of a coronavirus outbreak aboard the Roosevelt.
The fallout: Crozier was fired after the attached memo — which warned that “sailors do not have to die” — leaked to the press.
